records.addlTxt:
Defendant Timothy Haines in court with attorney Robert Buckett.  Defendant Timothy Haines in custody.  Thomas Potter for Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.  Court further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.   The Court sentenced defendant to serve 10  MONTHS in the House of Corrections,  with credit for 72 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions:
-Restitution set at $0  
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment.  
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Anger management and cooperate with program
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation
-Pay all supervision fees; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment 
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment 
-No contact with  Earvin R., Tiffani J., Linda C.  
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or illegal drugs
-No use of prescription medications without a valid prescription 
-Court will grant expungement if defendant was substantially compliant with terms and conditions of probation 
-Defendant to perform 50 hours of community service
